original_prompt:
Can you provide a SQL query that retrieves a list of all Artificial Intelligence TED Talks and includes the following information:
- Full name of the speaker
- Title of the talk
- Detailed description of the talk
- Exact URL of the TED Talk
- Date and time of the talk in ISO 8601 format
- Duration of the talk in seconds
- Total number of views the talk has received as of the time of data collection.
Assuming the data is stored in a SQL database, the query may look something like:
SELECT
speaker.full_name,
talk.title,
talk.description,
talk.url,
talk.date_time,
talk.duration,
talk.views
FROM
talks AS talk
INNER JOIN speakers AS speaker
ON talk.speaker_id = speaker.id
WHERE
talk.topic = 'Artificial Intelligence'
ORDER BY
talk.date_time DESC;
optimized_prompt: Write a single SQL query that retrieves all TED Talks on Artificial Intelligence, returning the speaker's full name, talk title, description, URL, date and time in ISO 8601 format, duration in seconds, and view count. Assume the database has tables 'talks' and 'speakers' with columns: talks.speaker_id, talks.topic, talks.title, talks.description, talks.url, talks.date_time, talks.duration, talks.views; speakers.id, speakers.full_name. The query should join these tables, filter by topic 'Artificial Intelligence', and order by date_time descending. Output only the SQL query, no explanations.
